<section class="seo-content-block" style="max-width:860px;margin:3rem auto;padding:0 1.5rem;font-family:inherit;">

  <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem;">
    What is Ayurvedic Hair Oil?
  </h2>
  <p style="line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
    Ayurveda — the 5,000-year-old Indian system of natural healing — has long 
    used plant-based oils to nourish the scalp, strengthen roots, and promote 
    healthy hair growth. At ByErim, we've taken those ancient principles and 
    combined them with modern cosmetic science to create a luxury hair oil 
    that actually works.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem;">
    Why Choose ByErim's Ayurvedic Hair Oil?
  </h2>
  <ul style="line-height:2;padding-left:1.2rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
    <li>🌿 <strong>100% natural ingredients</strong> — no sulphates, no parabens, no silicones</li>
    <li>🏆 <strong>Award-winning formula</strong> — recognised by the UK beauty industry</li>
    <li>💧 <strong>Vegan &amp; cruelty-free</strong> — certified and proudly so</li>
    <li>🧴 <strong>Unisex</strong> — works for all hair types, textures, and lengths</li>
    <li>🇬🇧 <strong>UK brand</strong> — founded by Erim Kaur, British-Indian haircare expert</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem;">
    Key Ayurvedic Ingredients
  </h2>
  <p style="line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
    Our formulas draw on Ayurvedic staples including <strong>amla (Indian gooseberry)</strong>, 
    known to strengthen hair follicles; <strong>castor oil</strong>, used for centuries 
    to boost scalp circulation; and <strong>rosemary</strong>, now backed by clinical 
    studies as a natural DHT blocker. Every ingredient earns its place.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem;">
    How to Use Ayurvedic Hair Oil
  </h2>
  <ol style="line-height:2;padding-left:1.2rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
    <li>Apply 3–5 drops to your fingertips</li>
    <li>Massage into the scalp in slow circular motions for 2–3 minutes</li>
    <li>Work any remaining oil through the mid-lengths and ends</li>
    <li>Leave for at least 30 minutes — or overnight for deep nourishment</li>
    <li>Wash out with ByErim Shampoo</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem;">
    Ayurvedic Hair Oil FAQ
  </h2>

  <details style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">Can I use ayurvedic hair oil every day?</summary>
    <p style="line-height:1.8;padding-top:0.5rem;">
      Yes — ByErim Hair Oil is lightweight enough to use daily as a finishing oil, 
      or 2–3 times per week as a pre-wash treatment. Listen to your hair.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">Is ayurvedic hair oil good for hair growth?</summary>
    <p style="line-height:1.8;padding-top:0.5rem;">
      Ayurvedic oils improve scalp circulation, reduce breakage, and strengthen 
      follicles — all of which support healthy hair growth. Consistent use over 
      8–12 weeks is where most people see visible results.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">What's the difference between ayurvedic hair oil and regular hair oil?</summary>
    <p style="line-height:1.8;padding-top:0.5rem;">
      Ayurvedic hair oils are rooted in holistic plant-based traditions and 
      typically contain botanicals like amla, brahmi, or bhringraj. Regular 
      hair oils may focus purely on conditioning. ByErim blends both worlds — 
      Ayurvedic heritage with modern cosmetic formulation.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">Is ByErim hair oil suitable for all hair types?</summary>
    <p style="line-height:1.8;padding-top:0.5rem;">
      Yes. Our formula works on straight, wavy, curly, and coily hair. 
      It's also suitable for colour-treated and chemically processed hair.
    </p>
  </details>

</section>
